properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 2 at 5:30PM MST until February 3 at 4:00PM MST by NWS Flagstaff AZ
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 20 to 35 mph with gusts to 55 mph
expected. Winds becoming westerly by mid day Monday.

* WHERE...All of Navajo and Apache counties north of I-40 as
well as the Gap, Bitter Springs, Marble Canyon and the Page
areas.

* WHEN...From 10 PM this evening to 4 PM MST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. In
addition, winds this strong can make driving difficult,
especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A period of light snow showers is likely
to combine with these strong winds Monday.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM THIS EVENING TO 4 PM MST MONDAY
